ose that address new challenges: linguistic annotation practice, fieldwork and interaction with speech communities, developments and challenges in archiving digital data, multimedia lexicon applications, corpora from endangered languages as a source for primary-data typology, as well as specific areas of linguistic analysis that are raised in documentary linguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLanguage and languages. 0aLanguage obsolescence. 4aBedrohte Sprachen. 4aTypologie /Sprache. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBroeder, Daan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCablitz, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeyer, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaig, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaig, Geoffrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHimmelmann, Nikolaus P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHovdhaugen, Even, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJung, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalau, Catriona Hyslop, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargetts, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNau, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNau, Nicole, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNæss, Åshild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPawley, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchnell, Stefan, econtr